						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone on the river bank.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1206.</p>						

						<p>This record dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 11[29]</hi> (current), <hi rend="bold">Kshaya, Kārtika, Pūrṇimā, Monday,</hi> states that a hero named <hi rend="bold">Kāḷeya</hi> died in a fight near <hi rend="bold">Ānevari,</hi> with a certain <hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍya,</hi> while <hi rend="italic">Rājaguru</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kalyāṇas11aktidēva</hi> was sending his brother <hi rend="bold">Dhruvēśvaradēva</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Śrīparvata.</hi> It is also stated that some land was granted in recognition of his valour.</p>						

						<p>The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> cited corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1206, October 18, Wednesday</hi> (not Monday as stated in the record). </p>						

						</summary>
